1. **Best Step-4 anti-circuit packet choices**
   The repo does not pin one concrete `k,p,q` triple, so the best-grounded answer is family-shape level, not a single wavevector sample. The strongest anti-circuit tests are: a minimal exact helical support family with one or two linked triads plus mandatory conjugate completion, because that is the cleanest way to stress coefficient rigidity and sign patterns; a full canonical one-shell-bridge packet family with all forced mirror, companion, feedback, and cross-scale modes included from the start, because that is the right object for leakage lower bounds; and a scale-separated finite-window family with tiny-trigger initial data or small tails, because the itinerary candidate lives or dies on ordered event times rather than on one-shot coefficient matching. The planning chains and Step-4 goal explicitly support those shapes, even though they stop short of fixing one explicit wavevector tuple. [Planner chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-01.md), [Planner chain 02](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md), [Refined chain 03](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md), [Step-4 Goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md).

2. **Best honest pro-circuit packet choices**
   Use the same frozen packet object, but bias the geometry and helicity toward the opposite conclusion: engineered helical sign patterns, sparse triad geometries, scale-separated packets, and families where leakage exists but is dynamically negligible. For `Template-Defect Near-Closure`, the pro-case is a sign-pattern and coefficient-ratio configuration that makes the fixed Tao-like template easier to match. For `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, the pro-case is a sparse or dynamically negligible leakage family that keeps `L_tot` and the class budgets small. For `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`, the pro-case is a scale-separated family whose trigger stays tiny until the frozen threshold order is reached. The attack and judgment on Chain 01 explicitly say the audit is biased unless it includes those favorable cases too. [Attack chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md), [Judgment chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md), [Step-4 Goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md).

3. **Adverse cases and what they stress**
   Beltrami cancellation is the special-case zero-stretching limit, with `ω × u = 0` and `p = -|u|^2/2 + const`; it stresses whether the template and leakage sheets remain meaningful when the desired nonlinear signal collapses, so it mainly tests coercivity and denominator stability. Mirror-mode completion is not optional bookkeeping in this branch, because real-valuedness forces the conjugate packet; it stresses whether `L_mirror` and the full off-template ledger remain invariant under canonical completion. Nearly degenerate triads stress coefficient rigidity, because the exact triad coefficients are geometry- and helicity-determined and can become sign-indefinite or cancellation-prone. Tiny trigger modes stress the itinerary candidate directly, because the trigger is dynamically central while energetically negligible before threshold, so the exact event-order tuple can fail to materialize on the fixed window. [Atlas final report](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md), [Atlas exploration 002](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md), [Step-3 exploration 002 report](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-3/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT.md)

4. **Favorable cases and what they favor**
   Engineered helical sign patterns favor the coefficient-rigidity candidate, because they are the best local way to make the exact triad signs line up with the Tao hierarchy. Sparse triad geometries favor the leakage candidate, because they reduce forced spectator clutter and can make `L_tot` and the classwise budgets easier to keep small. Scale-separated packets favor the itinerary candidate, because they give the ordered threshold logic room to unfold on the frozen window. Families where leakage exists but is dynamically negligible favor the same leakage route as a possible honest pro-circuit outcome, because the leakage observable can stay small even if the packet is not perfectly isolated. The local planning record treats these as mandatory counterweights to the adverse set, not as after-the-fact rescues. [Attack chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-01.md), [Judgment chain 01](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md), [Step-4 Goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md)

5. **Frozen sheets that can be reused without retuning**
   `Template-Defect Near-Closure` can reuse the frozen role hierarchy `h_seed << h_clk < 1 < h_amp < h_rot, h_next`, the role norm, `lambda_tmpl`, `lambda_spec`, `T_act`, and the gate `G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`. `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` can reuse the frozen `D_on`/`D_off` split, the fixed spectator partition `mirror, companion, feedback, cross`, `L_tot`, the class budgets, and the same finite window `I = [0, T_act]`. `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` can reuse `theta_B < theta_C < theta_D < theta_E <= 1`, `Lambda_itin`, `kappa_rot`, the frozen sign sheet, the amplitude and phase anchors, and the gate `G_itin(P_n; I) = (t_clk, t_trig, t_rot, t_next; sign sheet; spectator pass/fail)`. The Step-3 taxonomy and the hard-sheet note both say these are legitimate predeclared pass/fail sheets only if the partition and normalization are frozen before scoring. [Step-2 Results](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-2/RESULTS.md), [Step-3 exploration 001 taxonomy](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/library-inbox/step-003-exploration-001-robustness-taxonomy.md), [Hard-sheet note](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/library/meta/exploration-goal-design/fix-the-class-partition-and-finite-window-normalization-before-writing-hard-admissibility-sheets.md)

6. **Non-aggregated diagnostic vectors to retain**
   The repo does not yet prescribe a numeric vector, but it does prescribe the structure. For `Template-Defect Near-Closure`, retain the ordered pair `(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)` and, if possible, the channel-resolved residuals for the five desired channels plus the forced spectators, instead of collapsing them to one score. For `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`, retain the full 5-tuple `(L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)` together with the raw numerator and denominator pieces `∫ D_on` and `∫ D_off^class`. For `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary`, retain the ordered event tuple `(t_clk, t_trig, t_rot, t_next)`, the sign sheet, the threshold-crossing flags for `B, C, D, E`, and the spectator pass/fail trace on the fixed window. That matches the Chain 03 instruction to keep a non-aggregated diagnostic vector and the Step-4 goal’s demand to separate exact-packet dossier data from summary outcomes. [Step-4 Goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md), [Refined chain 03](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-03.md), [Step-2 exploration 002 summary](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-002/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md)

7. **Step-5 readiness versus earlier negative memo**
   The local materials support a Step-5-readiness comparison after both the obstruction-facing dossier and the construction-facing dossier are run. They do not yet force an earlier negative memo. The reason is simple: Step 4 is explicitly defined as the place where the branch tests both anti-circuit and pro-circuit families and then decides whether Step 5 is well-posed, and Step 3 already says Chain Step 4 is well-posed. An earlier negative memo only becomes justified if Step 4 cannot be run without hidden asymptotics, uncontrolled regularity input, or if the itinerary candidate survives only by importing Tao’s averaged one-way behavior. On the current record, that threshold has not been reached. [Step-4 Goal](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-004/GOAL.md), [Step-3 Results](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/RESULTS.md), [Step-3 exploration 002 summary](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/steps/step-003/explorations/exploration-002/REPORT-SUMMARY.md)

