+4. Which downstream gates already recorded in the repo are concrete enough for
+   surviving post-repair candidates, and which seemingly plausible gates are
+   still vague, cosmetic, or bookkeeping-dependent?
+5. Which local meta-library or mission notes give reusable discipline for
+   rejecting cosmetic survivors and for naming the final negative bucket
+   correctly if a candidate fails on
+   `precision`,
+   `robustness`,
+   or
+   `usefulness`?
+6. Based on the local record alone, what is the minimum honest exploration
+   split for Step 5:
+   one repair-ledger exploration,
+   one itinerary split/discard exploration,
+   and one shortlist / Step-6-readiness exploration,
+   or a smaller set?
