+# Exploration 001 Summary
+
+## Goal
+
+Lock the only honest Step-5 repair sheet for
+`Template-Defect Near-Closure`
+and
+`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`.
+
+## What I Tried
+
+- Read the final Step-4 dossier and the landed pro-side arithmetic artifact.
+- Checked which friendly values actually saturate the old thresholds.
+- Repaired only those thresholds that still had unused friendly-side slack.
+
+## Outcome
+
+- `[INFERRED]` `Template-Defect Near-Closure` tightens to
+  `lambda_tmpl = 1/4`
+  and
+  `lambda_spec = 49/256`.
+- `[INFERRED]` `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` tightens to
+  `Lambda_tot = 1/4`,
+  `Lambda_mirror = 1/12`,
+  `Lambda_feedback = 1/16`,
+  `Lambda_cross = 1/24`,
+  while
+  `Lambda_companion = 1/12`
+  stays unchanged because `F_SS(1/12)` already saturates it.
+
+## Key Takeaway
+
+Step 5 can remove unused slack from both algebraic/leakage candidates without
+changing the packet sheet or inventing new witnesses.
+
+## Leads Worth Pursuing
+
+- Carry these repaired thresholds into the final shortlist.
+- Use them to judge whether any later downstream gate is genuinely stronger or
+  only bookkeeping.
+
+## Unexpected Findings
+
+- The controlling Step-4 record for Step 5 has to be the final Step-4 results,
+  not one narrower intermediate anti-dossier note.
+
+## Computations Worth Doing Later
+
+- None for this step beyond the already-landed pro-side arithmetic check.
